
[1]gown

   GOWN, n.

   1. A woman;s upper garment.

   2. A long loose upper garment or robe, worn by professional men, as
   divines, lawyers, students, &c., who are called men of the gown or
   gownmen. It is made of any kind of cloth worn over ordinary clothes,and
   hangs down to the ankles or nearly so.

   4. The dress of peace, or the civil magistracy; cedant arma togoe.

   He Mars deposed, and arms to gowns made yield.
